events.name: Battery Manufacturing Supply Chain
events.wd_description: The battery manufacturing supply chain has three main parts: cell manufacturing, module manufacturing, and pack assembly. These stages can be conducted in the same place or at different locations, and the supply chain dynamics vary based on location and logistics.
events.description: The battery manufacturing supply chain has three main parts: cell manufacturing, module manufacturing, and pack assembly. These stages can be conducted in the same place or at different locations, and the supply chain dynamics vary based on location and logistics.

events.name: Cell Manufacturing
events.wd_description: Cell manufacturing involves producing the electrochemical cells, which consist of a cathode, an anode, and an electrolyte. This stage adds significant value to the battery.
events.description: Cell manufacturing involves producing the electrochemical cells, which consist of a cathode, an anode, and an electrolyte. This stage adds significant value to the battery.

events.name: Cathode Production
events.wd_description: Cathode production involves creating the positive electrode for the battery cell, which is crucial for the battery's performance.
events.description: Cathode production involves creating the positive electrode for the battery cell, which is crucial for the battery's performance.

events.name: Anode Production
events.wd_description: Anode production involves creating the negative electrode for the battery cell, facilitating the flow of lithium ions.
events.description: Anode production involves creating the negative electrode for the battery cell, facilitating the flow of lithium ions.

events.name: Electrolyte Production
events.wd_description: Electrolyte production involves creating the medium that allows lithium ions to move between the cathode and anode, enabling battery discharge.
events.description: Electrolyte production involves creating the medium that allows lithium ions to move between the cathode and anode, enabling battery discharge.

events.name: Module Manufacturing
events.wd_description: Module manufacturing involves assembling multiple cells into a module, with the number of cells varying by manufacturer and cell type. This stage contributes to about 11 percent of the total cost of a finished lithium-ion battery pack.
events.description: Module manufacturing involves assembling multiple cells into a module, with the number of cells varying by manufacturer and cell type. This stage contributes to about 11 percent of the total cost of a finished lithium-ion battery pack.

events.name: Cell Assembly
events.wd_description: Cell assembly involves arranging individual cells into a module, preparing them for integration into battery packs.
events.description: Cell assembly involves arranging individual cells into a module, preparing them for integration into battery packs.

events.name: Module Assembly
events.wd_description: Module assembly involves putting together the modules using the assembled cells, readying them for pack assembly.

events.name: Pack Assembly
events.wd_description: Pack assembly involves combining modules into a complete battery pack, which is often done near the vehicle assembly location due to transportation costs.

events.name: Module Integration
events.wd_description: Module integration involves fitting together modules into a structure that can be used in a battery pack.

events.name: Final Pack Assembly
events.wd_description: Final pack assembly involves assembling the integrated modules into the final battery pack, ready for installation in electric vehicles.
